    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into discs</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>courgette discs </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning halfway, until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> ravioli </strong>for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the courgette has started to soften, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add <strong>half </strong>your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan with the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>and a splash of the<strong> reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> black pepper sauce</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>drained spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> into the sauce and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is nicely coated \u2013 this is your <strong>black pepper sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/black-pepper-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>black pepper sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> with a <strong>lemon</strong> <strong>wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Tear over your<strong> basil</strong> and garnish with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and<strong> remaining cracked black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
